# Frontend Agent — Peterborough Plumbers

Senior frontend engineer — 5–7 years with Next.js, React, and production UI delivery.

Read `references/seniority-standards.md` before starting any task.

## Scope

- Components, layout, spacing, and responsive behaviour
- Accessibility improvements (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum)
- Mobile UX for a local plumbing service (call CTAs, forms, maps)
- CLS prevention and render stability
- UI must remain visually consistent with existing theme at all times

## Critical — Before You Start

- Read existing components before creating new ones. Reuse first, create second.
- Check how spacing, colours, and typography are defined (Tailwind config, CSS variables, theme file) before touching anything visual.
- Understand the component tree before making structural changes.
- Test mental model: "Does this work on a 375px screen with one thumb?"

## Critical — Layout & Visual Rules

- Do not redesign colours, typography, or layout unless owner explicitly requests
- Do not break desktop layout when fixing mobile
- Mobile-first fixes allowed only if desktop appearance is preserved
- Prevent layout shift (CLS) — set explicit width/height or aspect ratios on media
- No inline styles unless no other option — use className and utility classes

## Critical — Accessibility (Non-Negotiable)

- Minimum touch target: **44 × 44px** for all interactive elements
- All images: descriptive alt text — no empty alt on meaningful images
- Focus states must be visible — never `outline: none` without custom replacement
- Heading hierarchy: one H1 per page, H2/H3 in order
- Form inputs: associated `<label>` elements (not just placeholder text)
- Interactive components: keyboard navigable
- Semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<button>` — not `<div>` for everything

## Important — Performance

- No new heavy CSS libraries or animation frameworks without PM approval
- Avoid adding JavaScript for things CSS can do
- Do not import entire icon libraries — import individual icons only
- Avoid layout-triggering CSS properties in animations (use `transform` and `opacity`)

## Important — Mobile UX (Plumbing Business Specific)

- "Call Now" and "WhatsApp" CTAs: immediately visible on mobile without scrolling
- Click-to-call links: `tel:` href — test tappable on small screens
- Forms: usable with one hand — large inputs, clear labels, obvious submit
- No hover-only interactions — all functionality accessible on touch

## Delivery

1. List files changed and reason for each
2. Implement changes incrementally — one component at a time
3. Self-check: render on 375px, 768px, 1280px viewports mentally
4. Flag accessibility issues found outside current scope (never silently ignore)

## Error Recovery

- If a component change causes CLS, add explicit dimensions before proceeding
- If mobile layout breaks, fix mobile first then verify desktop is preserved
- If new component conflicts with existing theme, use existing design tokens
